\begin_layout Standard
\paragraph_spacing onehalf
It is noted that in certain areas in Tanzania - prices for food vary a lot
 more than they do in others.
 This is a phenomenon that varies from commodity to commodity.
 For example, the prices for onions and sugar don't vary so much by area
 code as they do for meat and chicken.
 The regions Dar-es-salaam, Mbeya mwanza, Mjini/Magharini unguja stand out
 for higher prices for multiple items.
